# scikit-image Contribution Conventions

These conventions are loaded from `profiles/scikit-image.yaml` — the team-owned
source of truth. When reviewing or generating code in this workspace, enforce
these rules.

## Naming

- Functions and variables: `snake_case`
- Import convention: `import skimage as ski`

## Docstrings — NumPy Style (numpydoc)

Every public function MUST have a docstring with these sections:

```
Parameters
----------
image : (M, N) ndarray
    Description of the parameter.

Returns
-------
result : ndarray
    Description of the return value.

Examples
--------
>>> # Usage example here
```

- Array parameters MUST use shape notation: `(M, N)`, `(M, N, 3)`, etc.
- Do NOT use Google-style `Args:` / `Returns:` — this project uses numpydoc.

## Approved Directories

New source files may only be created in these directories:
- `skimage/color/`, `skimage/data/`, `skimage/draw/`
- `skimage/exposure/`, `skimage/feature/`, `skimage/filters/`
- `skimage/graph/`, `skimage/io/`, `skimage/measure/`
- `skimage/metrics/`, `skimage/morphology/`, `skimage/registration/`
- `skimage/restoration/`, `skimage/segmentation/`
- `skimage/transform/`, `skimage/util/`

## Forbidden Paths

NEVER import from or write to:
- `skimage/_shared/` — internal utilities, not part of the public API
- `skimage/_vendored/` — vendored third-party code
- `skimage/_build/` — build artifacts

## Deprecated APIs

Do NOT use these — suggest the replacement instead:
- `skimage.filters.median` → `skimage.filters.rank.median`
- `skimage.measure.marching_cubes_lewiner` → `skimage.measure.marching_cubes`
- `skimage.transform.estimate_transform` → `skimage.transform.AffineTransform.estimate`

## Testing

- Framework: pytest
- Test file naming: `test_*.py` in `{module}/tests/`
- Run tests with: `spin test`
- Every contribution MUST include tests with:
  - Shape preservation test
  - Dtype roundtrip test

## The CLI

Run `ob check <workspace>` to validate against these conventions deterministically.
Run `ob scaffold --task "..."` to create a convention-compliant workspace.
